    "id": "call-transcripts/objection-price-002.md",
    "content": "# Call Transcript — WON after Price Objection — objection-price-002\n\n> Sample transcript showing objection handling on price + financing.\n> Outcome: **Customer objected to cost, financing offered, booked consult.**\n\n**AI:** Thanks for calling [Shop Name], this is your AI assistant — how can I help?\n**Customer:** I got a quote for like $2,400 for a compressor and that's insane.\n**AI:** That's a big number, I get it — a compressor is one of the priciest parts of the\nsystem. Two things: I can have our tech re-verify it's actually the compressor and not a\ncheaper fix, and if it is, we have 0% financing for 12 months on repairs over $1,000, so it\ndoesn't hit all at once. Want me to set up the visit?\n**Customer:** How much is the visit?\n**AI:** $89 for the diagnostic, and it's waived if you move forward with the repair the same\nvisit. So if it's the compressor and you book it, the $89 comes off.\n**Customer:** Okay… and the financing is really 0%?\n**AI:** Yes — 0% APR for 12 months on approved credit for repairs over $1,000. Want the 2pm\nor the 4pm tomorrow?\n**Customer:** Let's do 4pm.\n**AI:** Booked for 4pm tomorrow. Sending your confirmation text now.\n\n## Pattern notes\n- Validated the sticker shock instead of arguing.\n- Offered a second opinion (reduces \"ripped off\" fear) + financing (reduces payment fear).\n- Cited real, in-sheet numbers only ($89, 0%/12mo, $1,000 threshold).\n- Closed with a two-slot choice.\n- Source facts: `pricing/ac-repair-2024.md § Financing`, `§ Diagnostic Fee`.\n"
