    "id": "call-transcripts/winning-call-001.md",
    "content": "# Call Transcript — WON (Booked Same-Day) — winning-call-001\n\n> Sample transcript used as a pattern for how a good booking call flows.\n> Outcome: **Booked same-day AC repair, $89 diagnostic waived on repair.**\n\n**AI:** Thanks for calling [Shop Name], this is your AI assistant — how can I help today?\n**Customer:** My AC is blowing hot air and it's brutal in here.\n**AI:** Sorry you're dealing with that in this heat — I can get a tech out today. Is this for\nyour home or a business?\n**Customer:** Home.\n**AI:** Got it. What's the address, and the best callback number?\n**Customer:** 1420 SW 8th St, and my cell is 305-555-0142.\n**AI:** Perfect. Blowing hot usually means a refrigerant or capacitor issue — the tech will\ndiagnose it on site. The diagnostic is $89 and it's waived if you book the repair the same\nvisit. I've got a 2pm or a 4pm open today — which works better?\n**Customer:** 2pm.\n**AI:** Done — you're booked for 2pm today, [date]. I'm sending a text confirmation now with\nthe tech's ETA. Anything else?\n**Customer:** Nope, thank you.\n\n## Pattern notes (why it worked)\n- Led with empathy, moved fast to qualify (home/business → address → phone).\n- Named the likely issue but did NOT quote a fixed repair price — deferred to on-site.\n- Used the $89-waived line to lower resistance.\n- Offered exactly **two** concrete slots (choice, not open-ended).\n- Confirmed booking + SMS in one motion.\n"
