    "id": "faqs/common-objections.md",
    "content": "# FAQ: Top 10 Objections + Responses\n\n> Sample objection-handling scripts grounded in pricing/SOPs. The AI must cite the source\n> doc it pulls the supporting fact from (e.g. pricing or financing).\n\n## 1. \"That's too expensive.\"\nAcknowledge → reframe on value → offer financing.\n> \"I hear you. The diagnostic is just $89 and it's waived if you book the repair the same\n> visit, so you're not paying twice [Source: pricing/ac-repair-2024.md § Diagnostic Fee].\n> For bigger repairs we also have 0% financing for 12 months [Source: pricing/ac-repair-2024.md § Financing].\n> Want me to get a tech out to give you the exact number?\"\n\n## 2. \"I need to think about it.\"\nLower the commitment, add mild urgency.\n> \"Totally fair. The visit itself doesn't commit you to the repair — the tech just diagnoses\n> it and gives you the exact price, then it's your call. I've got a slot today; want me to\n> hold it so you're not waiting days in this heat?\"\n\n## 3. \"Can you come today?\"\nCheck calendar, offer real slots.\n> \"Let me check today's availability… I have [slot A] or [slot B]. Which works?\"\n> (Availability comes from the GoHighLevel calendar, never invented.)\n\n## 4. \"I'll just get another quote first.\"\n> \"Smart to compare. Our diagnostic gives you an itemized, exact quote you can compare\n> apples-to-apples — and it's waived if you move forward with us. Want me to book it?\"\n\n## 5. \"Why is there a diagnostic fee?\"\n> \"It covers the tech's time to properly diagnose the issue instead of guessing. And it's\n> waived if you book the repair on that same visit [Source: pricing/ac-repair-2024.md § Diagnostic Fee].\"\n\n## 6. \"Is this covered under warranty?\"\n> \"Depends on when it was installed — let me check. If we installed it, repairs carry a\n> 90-day labor warranty and parts are often 5–10 years [Source: sops/warranty-policy.md].\n> Let me book a quick warranty check so we confirm before you pay anything.\"\n\n## 7. \"My last company ripped me off.\"\nEmpathize → proof → low-risk next step.\n> \"I'm sorry that happened. Everything we quote is in writing and the diagnostic is only $89.\n> No surprise charges — the tech confirms the price before any work starts.\"\n\n## 8. \"Do you do free estimates?\"\n> \"For new-system installs, yes — the consult is free. For repairs there's an $89 diagnostic\n> that's waived if you book the repair same visit [Source: pricing/ac-repair-2024.md].\"\n\n## 9. \"It's making a weird noise but still works.\"\n> \"Better to catch it early — a small part now is cheaper than a compressor later. A tune-up\n> starts at $99 and the tech will pinpoint the noise [Source: pricing/ac-repair-2024.md § Maintenance / Tune-Up].\"\n\n## 10. \"How much for a whole new AC?\"\n> \"Installs vary by size and efficiency, so we do a free in-home consult to size it right and\n> give you an exact quote with financing options [Source: services/ac-installation.md].\n> Want me to set that up?\"\n"
