    "id": "pricing/ac-repair-2024.md",
    "content": "# AC Repair & Service Pricing (2024)\n\n> Sample pricing sheet. Replace with the shop's real numbers before production.\n> All prices are **starting-at / estimate ranges** — the tech confirms exact price on site.\n\n## Diagnostic Fee\n- **Standard diagnostic:** starting at **$89** (waived if repair is booked same visit)\n- **After-hours / weekend diagnostic:** starting at **$129**\n\n## Common AC Repairs (parts + labor, starting ranges)\n| Service | Starting At | Typical Range |\n|---|---|---|\n| Refrigerant recharge (per lb, R-410A) | $75/lb | $150–$450 |\n| Capacitor replacement | $129 | $129–$249 |\n| Contactor replacement | $149 | $149–$299 |\n| Condenser fan motor | $299 | $299–$650 |\n| Blower motor | $349 | $349–$750 |\n| Evaporator coil | $650 | $650–$1,600 |\n| Compressor (parts + labor) | $1,200 | $1,200–$2,800 |\n| Thermostat (standard) | $149 | $149–$349 |\n| Thermostat (smart / Wi-Fi) | $279 | $279–$499 |\n\n## Maintenance / Tune-Up\n- **Single-system AC tune-up:** starting at **$99**\n- **Annual maintenance plan (2 visits/yr):** starting at **$189/yr**\n\n## Financing\n- 0% APR for 12 months on repairs over $1,000 (approved credit)\n- Low monthly payment plans available on installs — see `services/ac-installation.md`\n\n## Rules for the AI\n- Never quote a fixed price. Always say \"starting at\" or give the range above.\n- If a repair isn't listed here, offer a diagnostic visit — do **not** invent a price.\n- The diagnostic fee is waived only if the customer books the repair on the same visit.\n"
