    "id": "sops/warranty-policy.md",
    "content": "# SOP: Warranty Policy\n\n> Sample warranty policy. Replace terms with the shop's real warranty before production.\n\n## Labor warranty\n- **Repairs:** 90-day labor warranty on any repair we perform.\n- **New system installs:** 2-year labor warranty (10-year on select premium installs).\n\n## Parts warranty\n- Manufacturer parts warranty typically **5–10 years** with product registration.\n- We register the equipment for the customer at time of install.\n\n## What's covered\n- Failure of a part we installed, under normal use, within the warranty window.\n- Return visit at no labor charge for a warrantied repair that recurs.\n\n## What's NOT covered\n- Damage from lack of maintenance, power surges, flooding, or third-party tampering.\n- Filters and consumables.\n\n## AI handling\n- If a customer asks \"is this covered under warranty?\" — pull this doc, confirm the window,\n  and if it's ambiguous, book a warranty-check visit rather than promising coverage.\n- Never promise a free repair without confirming the install date is on file in GoHighLevel.\n"
